      {
        "id": 2771956,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-12-14T00:05:12.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The Clos de la Baronne is owned by American investors, IIRC, and it produces a fatter, fleshier wine. The Clos de la Barre is one of the emblematic wines from the domaine from a superior terroir, and if I\u2019m not mistaken was the original lieu-dit bottled Meursault that started it all. It produces a wine with more tension and aging potential.</p>",
